@startuml journey-kid
' ============================================================
' Zoomed User-Experience Flow: Kid Surface
'
' Product/UX-clarity altitude for the child-facing app only (route tree "/").
' Node fill: white = shipped today, rose = planned (not yet built).
'
' Source screens:
'   frontend/src/router.tsx  (kid route tree: /kids, /library/:profileId, /read/...;
'     DeviceAuthorizedRoute wraps the whole tree, ADR-014)
'   frontend/src/auth/DeviceAuthorizedRoute.tsx, auth/deviceGrant.ts (ADR-014:
'     local device-grant check, Supabase-free)
'   frontend/src/landing/LandingPage.tsx  (device-state-aware Kids door)
'   frontend/src/kid/ProfilePickerPage.tsx
'   frontend/src/library/LibraryPage.tsx, BookCard.tsx, StarRating.tsx
'   frontend/src/library/RequestStory.tsx  (child-initiated request, WS-B;
'     shipped, mounted on the library page -- see api/story_requests.py)
'   frontend/src/reader/Reader.tsx, ReaderRoute.tsx, ConflictDialog.tsx
'   Phase 4a mobile UI wireframe concept spec (PR #47, shipped; the source doc under
'     docs/superpowers/specs/ was retired as scratch output once its work merged)
' ============================================================

title Kid-Surface Journey\n(child-facing app "/"; rose = planned, not yet built)

skinparam defaultFontName "Roboto"
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam roundCorner 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #5a3e28
skinparam ArrowFontColor #5a3e28
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FFFDF8
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #f8f3e8
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #F1E9D8
skinparam NoteBorderColor #c9b48f

|#F0D9B8|Child|
start
:Open the app
(tap the Kids door);
if (Is this device authorized?\n(local device-grant check,\nno guardian login, no Supabase\nround-trip)) then (yes)
else (no)
  :Guardian signs in and
  authorizes this device;
  note right: /guardian/login?intent=authorize-device  •  shipped\nADR-014 -- mints a 90-day device grant, then\ndrops back here; a returning authorized device\nnever sees this step again
endif
:Tap my avatar
(2-column picker,
dashed circle if none);
note right: /kids  (Profile Picker)  •  shipped

:See "new story ready!"
on my avatar;
note right: status pill  •  shipped

:Open my Library
(Continue Reading hero
+ "More to Explore" shelf);
note right: /library/:profileId  •  shipped

:Tap "Request a story"
and say what it's about
(or "Continue this story"
on a series book);
note right: RequestStory on the library page  •  shipped\nsurfaces to a guardian/admin to approve or decline\n(no moderation detail ever shown to the child)
:See my own requests'
friendly status
(Waiting / Yay! / Not this time);
note right: shipped  •  "My requests" list

:Pick a book;

' error exits are real, tested paths
if (Is the story available?) then (yes)
  :Reader opens the story;
  note right: /read/:profileId/:storybookId/:version  •  shipped
elseif (link is malformed) then
  :See a friendly exit,
  not a dead end;
  note right: shipped (reader.spec: malformed link)
  stop
else (story is missing)
  :See "not found",
  not the offline copy;
  note right: shipped (reader.spec: missing story)
  stop
endif

repeat :read a passage;
  :Read the passage
  (serif, generous spacing);
  :Make a choice
  (some choices stay hidden
  until the story-state allows);
  note right: state-gated visibility  •  shipped
  if (Am I online?) then (yes)
    :My progress saves as I go;
  else (offline)
    :Keep reading from the
    downloaded copy, progress
    waits in a queue;
    note right: offline-first  •  shipped
    :On reconnect it syncs;
    if (Did another device
    change it too?) then (yes, clash)
      :Choose which progress to keep
      (mine / the newer one);
      note right: ConflictDialog  •  shipped
    else (no)
    endif
  endif
repeat while (More story to read?) is (yes) not (reached an ending)

:See the ending screen
(restart, or "back to my books");
note right: ending screen  •  shipped\n(restart + back to library, no rating here)
:Go back to my Library;
:Rate a book by tapping its stars
on the shelf;
note right: StarRating on BookCard  •  shipped\n(rating lives in the library, not the reader)
stop

legend bottom
  |= Node |= Meaning |
  |<back:#FFFDF8>  white  </back>| Shipped in the kid app today |
  |<back:#F3D9D4>  rose   </back>| Planned, not yet built |
  The kid surface is a separate route tree from the guardian console and shares
  no navigation. ADR-014: the whole tree sits behind a local device-grant check
  (DeviceAuthorizedRoute), not a per-page gate, and stays Supabase-free.
  See journey-guardian for the parent side, seq-device-grant for the mint/verify/
  revoke mechanics, journey-end-to-end for the whole loop, and journey-dev-coverage
  for test coverage.
endlegend

@enduml
